The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Monday, December 16, 2002 				 Focus on digital and animation graphics
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								Seoul, Dec. 15: Sang-Chul Lee, minister of information and communications, invited Indian software entrepreneurs and companies to work together to become world leaders in digital and animation graphics.																								He also asked Korean companies involved in digital and animation graphics to set up research and development centres in India. Speaking to visiting media persons from India and Singapore, Lee said, We have the hardware strength and India has proved its leadership in software. If both the business sectors can join hands, we can become leaders in the world of digital and animation graphics.																								He said the wide band code division multiple access (WCDMA) will be launched next year and a few companies have already invested money in the project.
